{
  "texts": [
    "The essence of parameter estimation is to learn the mapping from the received signal R to the parameter space Ω, i.e., F: R → Ω, which can be effectively modeled by the AI techniques.",
    "Naoumi et al. [217] developed a DL-based algorithm to achieve joint AoA and AoD estimation for bistatic ISAC networks.",
    "Specifically, the OFDM waveform was used for dual functionality, and the transmitter and receiver of ISAC were separated.",
    "The authors developed a complex-valued neural network to deal with the estimated channels instead of the raw data as input, and used the MSE as the loss function.",
    "Their proposed DL-based algorithm can achieve comparable performance with much lower computational complexity than the traditional algorithms."
  ]
}